{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Each MRS observation for a stellar object contains multiple single-exposures.",
    "According to the observation plan of MRS, the duration of each single-exposure is about 1200 seconds; NT survey takes 3 single-exposures for each observation, and TD survey takes 3-8 single-exposures (Liu et al, 2020).",
    "In practical observations, more or less single-exposures are also possible.",
    "These single-exposure spectra are then coadded to obtain the spectral data with higher single-to-noise ratio.",
    "Both the single-exposure spectra and the coadded spectrum of one MRS observation are stored in the same FITS data file and share the same obsid (unique LAMOST observation identifier)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "According to the observation plan of MRS, the duration of each single-exposure is about 1200 seconds; NT survey takes 3 single-exposures for each observation, and TD survey takes 3-8 single-exposures (Liu et al, 2020)."
  ]
}